Now, can the encodeData(s) be in a different order than the typehash?
for ref: I got a piece of code, where the developers have implemented it like: 

```bytes32 public immutable PERMIT_TYPEHASH = keccak256("Permit(address owner, address spender, uint256 value, uint256 deadline, uint8 v, bytes32 r, bytes32 s)");

bytes32 hashStruct = keccak256(abi.encode(PERMIT_TYPEHASH, owner, spender, value, nonces[owner]++, deadline));```
Like nonce was not defined in the typehash, but used in the hashStruct. Also the v, r and s are not used in the hashStruct
Is it all fine?
